{"title_page": "List of Roman Catholic churches in Leicester", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{construction}}\nThis is a list of [[Roman Catholic]] [[Church (building)|churches]] in the Deanery of Leicester. The Deanery of Leicester is part of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Nottingham]] and includes the communities of [[Leicester]], [[Braunstone Town|Braunstone]], [[New Parks]], [[Aylestone]], [[Eyres Monsell]], [[Wigston]], [[Netherhall]], [[Rushy Mead]], [[Beaumont Leys]], [[Knighton, Leicester|Knighton]], [[Oadby]], [[Birstall, Leicestershire|Birstall]], [[Rothley]], [[Market Harborough]], [[Husbands Bosworth]], [[Earl Shilton]], [[Hinckley]], [[Market Bosworth]], [[Lutterworth]], and [[Narborough, Leicestershire|Narborough]].  The current area dean is the Rev. Mgr. John Hadley.<ref>{{cite web|title=Parishes|publisher=Diocese of Nottingham|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes}}</ref> The current bishop is Patrick Joseph McKinney from the Diocese of Nottingham.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Bishop|publisher=Diocese of Nottingham|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/bishop}}</ref>\n\n==Churches==\nThere are 15 current parishes operating in the Deanery of Leicester.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:95%\"\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Church name'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"10%\" |'''Image'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"35%\" |'''Location'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25\" |'''Description'''\n|-\n| [[Holy Cross Priory, Leicester|Holy Cross Priory]]\n|[[File:Holy Cross Priory, Leicester.jpg|120px]]\n|Wellington Street\n|[[Dominican Order|Dominican]] [[priory]] established in 1882, re-establishing Dominican presence in Leicester, which had existed from 1247 to 1538.  The Dominicans then established local parish churches of the area.  The priory church was rebuilt during 1929-58.<ref name=hcp-history>{{cite web|url=https://www.holycrossleicester.org/106-2/the-history-of-our-parish/ |title=The History of Our Parish |publisher=Holy Cross Priory |accessdate=11 April 2020|}}</ref>\n|-\n|Immaculate Conception\n|\n|54 New Street, [[Oadby]]\n|<ref>https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes/immaculate-conception-oadby</ref>\n|-\n|Most Blessed Sacrament\n|\n|Gooding Avenue, Braunstone\n|Parish church located in [[Braunstone Town|Braunstone]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Most Blessed Sacrament, Braunstone, Leicester|publisher=Diocese of Nottingham|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes/most-blessed-sacrament-gooding-avenue}}</ref>\n|-\n|Mother of God\n|\n|New Parks Boulevard, [[New Parks]]\n|Parish church serving the communities of New Parks and Glenfield<ref>{{cite web|title=Home|publisher=Mother of God Roman Catholic Church|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=http://motherofgodleicester.co.uk/index.php}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=About Us|publisher=Mother of God Roman Catholic Church|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=http://motherofgodleicester.co.uk/index.php/about-us}}</ref>\n|-\n|Our Lady of Good Counsel\n|\n|Gleneagles Avenue, Rushey Mead\n|A modernist church in shape and structure set in a suburban housing estate; built in 1975 based on design by Reynolds and Scott.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leicester in 50 Buildings|author=Stephen Butt|publisher=Amberly Publishing|year=2016|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FCwbDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT125&lpg=PT125&dq=our+lady+of+good+counsel+leicester&source=bl&ots=T294WnvX4k&sig=ACfU3U17b_NsrDoREezNLo1nbbRwqXcmLg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiDl5K5oOHoAhV5HzQIHTTuDV44ChDoATAEegQICxAu#v=onepage&q=our%20lady%20of%20good%20counsel%20leicester&f=false}}(entry no. 45)</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Our Lady of Good Counsel, Rushey Mead, Leicester|publisher=Diocese of Nottingham|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes/our-lady-of-good-counsel-rushey-mead}}</ref>\n|-\n|Our Lady of the Rosary\n|\n|Armadale Road, Netherall\n|A Catholic church.<ref>https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes/rosary-church-netherhall</ref>\n\n|-\n|Sacred Heart Church and Voluntary Academy\n|\n|25 Mere Road\n|Catholic church and school; brick church structure with twin Romanesque towers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sacred Heart Church|publisher=Sacred Heart Voluntary Academy|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=https://www.sacredheart.leicester.sch.uk/our-church-and-catholic-life/sacred-heart-church#}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Anne's\n|\n|Abingdon Road\n|Catholic church operated by the [[Society of Pius X]]<ref>{{cite web|title=St. Anne's Roman Catholic Church|publisher=The Society of Pius X|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=http://www.latin-mass.org.uk/page_photos.htm}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Edward the Confessor\n|\n|633 Aylestone Road, Aylestone\n|A Catholic church.<ref>[https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes/st-edward-the-confessor-leicester]</ref>\n|-\n|St. Mary's and St. John Bosco\n|\n|Countesthorpe Road, Wigston<br>Pasley Road, [[Eyres Monsell]]\n|Catholic parish operating out of two churches (formerly two parishes) serving the communities of Wigston, Blaby, and Countesthorpe<ref>{{cite web|title=About the Parishes of St Mary's and St John Bosco|publisher=St. Mary's and St. John Bosco|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=http://www.stmaryswigston.org.uk/about_us.html}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Joseph\n|\n|Uppingham Road\n|A Catholic church.<ref>[http://stjoseph-leicester.btck.co.uk/]</ref>\n|-\n|[[St Patrick's Catholic Church, Leicester|St. Patrick]] \n|\n|Beaumont Leys Lane\n|<ref>[http://www.saintpatrick-leicester.co.uk/]</ref> Romanesque-style church built in 1959, of parish established in 1854.\n|-\n|St. Peter\n|\n|21 Hinckley Road\n|A Catholic church.<ref>[http://www.stpetersleicester.org.uk/]</ref>\n|-\n|St. Piux X\n|\n|52 Leicester Road, Narborough\n|<ref>https://www.dioceseofnottingham.uk/parishes/st-pius-x-narborough</ref>\n|-\n|[[St Thomas More's Catholic Church, Leicester|St. Thomas More]]\n|[[File:Saint Thomas More, Knighton, Leicester - geograph.org.uk - 455071.jpg|80px]]\n|Knighton Road, Knighton\n|Parish established in 1947; the church was designed and built during 1948-52.  Designed in a stripped basilican style; its distinctive broad west tower is a local landmark.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Our Churches|publisher=Knighton & Oadby Catholic Parishes|accessdate=April 11, 2020|url=http://www.le2catholicparishes.info/}}</ref>\n|}\n\nIn addition, there is a Polish Catholic church located on Wakerley Road in Leicester. It operates out of a parish established in 1948 that celebrated its 70th anniversary in 2018.<ref>http://www.leicesterpolonia.co.uk/</ref>\n\n==Former churches==\nThere was a church named St. Michael's, of one of Leicester's oldest parishes, which was demolished by about 1450.  \"Very little is known\" about the church. It was perhaps located near what is now Vine Street and Elbow Lane.  This was in the northeast part of the medieval walled town, an area which is believed to have largely depopulated after devastation in the siege of 1173.<ref name=JDMartin90>{{cite web|url=https://www.le.ac.uk/lahs/downloads/1990/1990%20(64)%2021-25%20Martin.pdf |title=St Michael's Church and Parish, Leicester |author=Janet D. Martin |date=1990}}  PDF appears to be a print from a journal publication, details unclear.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Roman Catholic churches in the United Kingdom]]\n* [[Anglican churches in Leicester]]\n* [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Nottingham]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*''Return of Catholicism to Leicester 1746\u20131946'', by A. Kimberlin, 1946\n*[http://www.laurel-house.co.uk/where-leicester-has-worshipped.html Where Leicester has Worshipped]\n*[http://www2.le.ac.uk/departments/archaeology/research/projects/mapping-faith/places University of Leicester Archaeology and Ancient History Interactive Geo map of sites]\n\n[[Category:Lists of churches in England]]\n[[Category:Churches 